      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A telegram was received today by\nthe passenger department of the\nNorthern Pacific from General Pass\nenger Agent Charles S. Fee announc-\ning that a heavy rush of homeseekers\nis on the way here.\n\n\nTrain No. has left st. Paul every\nnight this week in two sections. The\nNorth Coast Limited has been crowd\ned to the utmost with the eager inn\nmigrants.\n\n\nThe number stopping off in Spo-\nkane has shown no decrease In the\nlast few days. Each road reports\nabout so tickets day deposited in\nthe local Office.\n\n\nA large number of immigrants are\npassing through to the Sound. while\nothers are jourpeying to points in\ncentral Washington."
    }
